description.narrative: At least 65% of villages in the most vulnerable areas adopt proper hygiene practices through the CLT approach, which contributes to Hygiene, Sanitation, Wash And Emergencies, Wash In Schools And Ecd Centres, Water, Water Supply. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2018, at least 80% of mothers and children, especially the most vulnerable, use the comprehensive integrated package of quality interventions for maternal, newborn and child health.
